Dictionary.Name: The Collaborative International Dictionary of English v.0.44

Definition.WordDefinition:
clickety-clack \clickety-clack\, clickety-click \clickety-click\n. a fast and rhythmic clicking sound, as of ``click-clack''; as, the clickety-clack of the typewriters.
Syn: clickety-clack. [WordNet 1.5]
clickety-clack n : a fast and rhythmic click-clack; "the clickety-clack of the typewriters" [syn: {clickety-click}]
